The Herald Arts Reporter Organisers for the Chibuku Neshamwari Dance festival finale have said preparations for this year’s edition are at an advanced stage. The finals will be held on August 13 at Harare Gardens and already 10 finalists are in the running for the first prize. This year will also see four lucky consumers driving away in brand new Nissan Navara single cabs. Delta Corporation general manager —corporate affairs, Patricia Murambinda said preparations for the finale were at an advanced stage. “Preparations have begun in earnest for the Chibuku Neshamwari National Final to be held on August 13 at Harare Gardens,” she said. “The competitions will be graced by well-known performing guest artists. It will truly be an exciting day, as we are also set to conduct the Chibuku Big 60 Promotion Grand Draw, where four consumers will win brand new Nissan Navara single cabs.” Murambinda said she was happy with the provincial level competitions as this brought diversity to the festival with different participants. “It has been an exciting Chibuku Neshamwari Dance Festival, where provincial competitions kicked off on May 28, this year,” she said. “The 10 provincial finals held were well attended, bringing a lot of excitement to our consumers.” Added to this, Chibuku’s 60th anniversary is being marked with new the Chibuku Super Banana Flavour from Delta Beverages. The new Chibuku banana flavoured variant is brewed with the same traditional taste profile as its sister brand, offering a unique and carbonated taste experience, with a well-balanced flavour.